true,"entry_ids":[""]}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"name","gloss":"Safar (the second month of the Islamic calendar)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be empty, to be devoid, to be vacant"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to empty, to void, to vacate, to evacuate, to free"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"empty, void, devoid, free from"},{"pos":"num","gloss":"zero","examples":[{"text":"Next: واحد, or ١ = 1"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dye yellow, to make yellow, to color yellow"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"brass"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"money"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of صَفِرَ (ṣafira) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"jaundice"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"plural of أَصْفَر (ʔaṣfar, “yellow”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to whistle"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hiss"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to chirp, to stridulate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to scream (of a siren)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to whistle"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hiss"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to chirp, to stridulate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to scream (of a siren)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From ص ف ر (ṣ f r, “void”), supposedly because pagan Arabs looted during this month and left the houses empty.\n\nSemantic loan from Sanskrit शून्य (śūnya), also with the original meaning of “empty, void”. Compare صَفْر (ṣafr, “empty, void”) (also صِفْر (ṣifr)).\n\nCausative from the root ص ف ر (ṣ f r), from which the color or defect adjective أَصْفَر (ʔaṣfar, “yellow”) also comes.\n\nRelated to أَصْفَر (ʔaṣfar, “yellow”), from the root ص ف ر (ṣ f r).\n\nIn its meaning \"jaundice\", related to أَصْفَر (ʔaṣfar, “yellow”), from the root ص ف ر (ṣ f r).\n\nInflected form.\n\nPresumably, originally an intensive of صَفَرَ (ṣafara, “to whistle, hiss, chirp”), later losing its intensive sense."},"ipa":["/sˤa.far/","/sˤifr/"]}